Step 1. Calculate the Gross Profit Margin from the income statement.  
• Gross Profit = 2,741,764.34  
• Total Revenue = 5,991,764.34  
• Gross Profit Margin = (Gross Profit ÷ Total Revenue) × 100  
  = (2,741,764.34 ÷ 5,991,764.34) × 100  
  ≈ 45.73%

Step 2. Calculate the Cash Flow to Debt Ratio using the cash flow and balance sheet.  
• Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities = 215,423.24  
• Total Current Liabilities (Debt) = Accounts Payable + Taxes Payable  
  = 825,000.00 + 299,588.25  
  = 1,124,588.25  
• Cash Flow to Debt Ratio = Net Cash Flow from Operating Activities ÷ Total Current Liabilities  
  = 215,423.24 ÷ 1,124,588.25  
  ≈ 0.19

Thus, the final answer is:
